            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-20T03:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-20T03:30:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.5018/9–2046: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commissioner in India</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-20T14:00:00+05:30">September 20, 1946—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>965. Pandit Jawaharlal Nehru is sending following personal message to Acting
                    Secretary through Agency General: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In view of very serious food situation in India which is being
                            aggravated by delay in arrival of promised allotments due to shipping
                            strikes in America, would earnestly request you and, through you, the
                            labour leaders to permit and arrange for earliest despatch of food ships
                            to India. We would be very grateful to you and to the labour leaders
                            concerned if they will make a special exception in favour of sending
                            food grains abroad which will bring urgently needed relief to millions
                            of people”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Am sure Nehru would appreciate widest publicity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Merrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
